
Patterns in Number Problem:

1. Using Remainder (num % 10), Quotient (num / 10), or Power (2^n, 10^n) concepts:
  1.1. CheckEvenOddNumber – Uses remainder (num % 2).
  1.2. CountDigitsInNumber – Uses quotient (num / 10) repeatedly.
  1.3. ReverseNumber – Uses remainder (num % 10) and quotient.
  1.4. CheckPalindromeNumber – Reverse number + compare with original.
  1.5. CheckPrimeNumber – Uses loop & modulus (divisibility check).
  1.6. PrintPrimeNumbers1ToN – Loop from 1 to N, check primality.
  1.7. CheckPrimePalindrome – Combination of prime + palindrome check.

